Derry Mathews will challenge world lightweight champion Richar Abril in Liverpool on March 6.

Abril, who holds the WBA title, was due to face Anthony Crolla later this month but the Manchester fighter was attacked just before Christmas after interrupting a robbery.

As a result, Mathews, who beat Crolla in 2012, will step in for his first shot at a world title against the tricky Cuban.

